<br>
The question I have is this:<br>
I've seen many posts that refer to disarm and evade as skills that can be used via hotkeys.  Now, I'm new to the rogue thing, not new to eq, I just normally play casters...so many of the skills and things of this nature are new to me.  I thought that disarm and evade were just kind of automatic skills that went off during a battle.  Can someone please enlighten me on how this works? And are there other combat oriented skills I should be aware of that also work on hotkeys? Please be gentle, I came here for advice and not ridicule.  I just want up my pvp skills! Thanks in advance for anyone that can help)<br>
<br>
Tsyndria<br>
14th circle rogue<br>
Vallon Zek<br>
<br>
&quot;If wits were blades, you would have some dull weapons.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucircilly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Circilly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/23/01 3:48:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on evade and disarm</span><hr size=1> You won't get disarm till 27th, once you can train it then at your guildmaster you can put it as a hotkey to use in PvP.  It won't improve in PvP but if you practice it lots while fightings mobs it will become a handy skill.<br>
<br>
Evade is achieved by hitting hide while a mob is aggro on you.  The procedure involves turning off attack, hitting hide (note it can be interupted) and getting message your attempt to evade combat was successful etc, and then turning on attack again quickly before you lose hits on the mob.  Hide skill can be dragged from the ability list to the hotkey pad and then used by the corresponding numbers 0-9 etc.  Most rogues will set up a evade hotkey using a social  such as this<br>
<br>
Name: Evade<br>
/attack or /attack off I think works too<br>
/doability and the appropriate number here for hide (see EQ manual for details, 1-6 right left then down I think and then 7-10 as the last 4 under combat)<br>
/attack or /attack on<br>
<br>
When used during the fight this will then rapidly attempt an evade and resume combat with no time lost.<br>
<br>
Further queries should be directed to the training lounge, unless pvp specific.  The library and old posts are a vast store of knowledge, much is often retold as new rogues come forth with similar questions.  Good luck. <p>Circilly <BR>
Gnomish Pirate <BR>
